entities.name: ElizaOS
entities.description: An open-source operating system framework that facilitates blockchain interactions and leverages long-term OS development innovation. It aims to provide a robust platform for AI and blockchain projects.

entities.name: auto.fun
entities.description: A platform being revitalized within the Eliza ecosystem, intended to serve as a launchpad for AI startups and function as 'internet capital markets' for AI projects.

entities.name: Polygon zkEVM
entities.description: A Layer 2 scaling solution for Ethereum that uses zero-knowledge proofs to achieve high transaction throughput and low fees. It allows for EVM-compatible computation on a separate chain.

entities.name: Colony
entities.description: A decentralized platform for building and managing organizations, often used for token verification systems and DAO governance. Its website is colonylab.io.

entities.name: Uniswap
entities.description: A decentralized exchange protocol for token swaps on the Ethereum blockchain. It enables automated, decentralized exchange of ERC-20 tokens.

entities.name: OpenAI
entities.description: An artificial intelligence research laboratory focused on developing and promoting friendly AI. They are known for creating large language models like GPT.

entities.name: Anthropic
entities.description: An AI safety and research company that develops AI systems, including large language models like Claude. They focus on helpful, honest, and harmless AI.

entities.name: Cardano
entities.description: A proof-of-stake blockchain platform designed as a development framework for decentralized applications. It aims to be more sustainable, scalable, and interoperable than previous generation blockchains.

entities.name: Eli5
entities.description: An AI project or a concept within the ElizaOS ecosystem, possibly related to explaining complex topics simply. It is referred to as 'ai16z's brother' and is suggested for integration into the Eliza 1.0.0 terminal.

entities.name: ai16z
entities.description: A token within the ElizaOS ecosystem, discussed in the context of token utility, access to airdrops, investment opportunities, and governance. It is also referred to as '$Ai16z'.

entities.name: Claude 4
entities.description: A family of large language models developed by Anthropic, known for their advanced capabilities in natural language understanding and generation. They are designed to be helpful, harmless, and honest.

entities.name: Telegram
entities.description: A cloud-based instant messaging service with a focus on security and speed. It allows users to send text and voice messages, make voice calls, and share an unlimited number of media and files.

entities.name: Discord
entities.description: A freeware direct messaging and digital distribution platform designed for video gaming communities. Users communicate via voice calls, video calls, text messaging, and media sharing within virtual communities called 'servers'.

entities.name: Twitter
entities.description: A microblogging and social networking service where users post and interact with messages known as 'tweets'. It is now known as X.

entities.name: Ethereum
entities.description: A decentralized, open-source blockchain system that features smart contract functionality. Ether (ETH) is the native cryptocurrency of the platform.

entities.name: Neon
entities.description: A PostgreSQL-compatible database service, often used for storing and managing application data. It is accessible via a standard PostgreSQL driver.

entities.name: SQLite
entities.description: A C-language library that implements a small, fast, self-contained, high-reliability, full-featured, SQL database engine. It is most commonly used in embedded applications.

entities.name: The ELI5 Protocol
entities.description: A protocol related to the ELI5 agent, suggesting a system designed to explain complex concepts in a simple manner, often compared to explaining to a five-year-old.

entities.name: EDI5
entities.description: A token associated with the ElizaOS ecosystem, mentioned in discussions about potential price recovery following the v2 launch.

entities.name: ELI5 Token
entities.description: A token within the ElizaOS ecosystem, identified as ELI5 and discussed in relation to its price performance and potential recovery after the v2 launch.
